[[File:Boehmhouseback.JPG|thumb|Rear of the Boehm House]] The '''Boehm House''' is an historic house at 75 Arthur Kill Road in the [[Richmondtown, Staten Island|Richmondtown]] section of the borough of [[Staten Island]] in [[New York City]]. This 1750 house, relocated from Greenridge as a part of [[Historic Richmondtown]], was typical of rural New York during the [[American Revolution]]. Also on view in the house: an exhibit of early building techniques and restorations. It was designated a [[New York City Landmarks Preservation Commission|New York City landmark]] in 1969 as the "Boehm-Frost House".<ref>{{cite web|title=Boehm-Frost House (landmark designation report)|url=http://www.neighborhoodpreservationcenter.org/db/bb_files/BOEHM-FROST.pdf|publisher=New York City Landmarks Preservation Commission|accessdate=16 June 2014}}</ref>
