The '''Coalition of Socialist Forces''' (CSF) ([[Arabic]]: تحالف القوى الاشتراكية) is a coalition of five [[socialist]] and [[Left-wing politics|left-wing]] groups in [[Egypt]] formed on 10 May 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://english.ahram.org.eg/NewsContent/1/64/11855/Egypt/Politics-/Five-socialist-parties-unite-to-impact-Egyptian-po.aspx|title=Five socialist parties unite to impact Egyptian politics|publisher=Ahram Online|date=11 May 2011|accessdate=9 November 2013}}</ref> The different forces agreed to enter into a "socialist front" in order "to create a more dominant leftist force" in [[Egyptian Revolution of 2011|post-revolutionary Egypt]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://english.ahram.org.eg/NewsContent/1/64/11968/Egypt/Politics-/Egypts-leftist-front,-will-it-survive.aspx |title=Egypt's leftist front, will it survive?|publisher=Ahram Online|date=12 May 2011|accessdate=9 November 2013}}</ref> As of 31 May 2011, the CSF is reported to have a combined membership of over 5,000 members.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://socialistworker.org/2011/05/31/new-shape-of-the-struggle|title=The new shape of the struggle in Egypt|publisher=Socialist Worker|date=31 May 2011|accessdate=9 November 2013 }}</ref>
