{{Infobox book | name = Edmonds Cookery Book | image = Edmonds Cookery Book.jpg | caption = 2008 centenary edition | alt = | title_orig = | orig_lang_code = | title_working = | translator = | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = New Zealand | language = English | subject = | genre = | published = | media_type = Print | awards = | dewey = 641.5 | congress = | preceded_by = | followed_by = | wikisource = }}
The '''''Edmonds Cookery Book''''' is a [[recipe book]] focusing on traditional [[New Zealand cuisine]]. It was first published as ''The Sure to Rise Cookery Book'' in 1908<ref name="nzhist">{{cite web|url=http://www.nzhistory.net.nz/media/photo/edmonds-cookbook|title=The Edmonds Cookbook|publisher=New Zealand Ministry for Culture and Heritage|accessdate=2009-02-17}}</ref> as a marketing tool by [[baking powder]] manufacturer [[Thomas Edmonds (manufacturer)|Thomas Edmonds]] (today part of [[Goodman Fielder]]), but it is now known as a [[Kiwiana|Kiwi icon]].
The front cover shows the old factory on Ferry Road in [[Linwood, New Zealand|Linwood]], [[Christchurch]] (since demolished) and their slogan "Sure to Rise". Only two copies of the first edition are known to survive.<ref name="nzhist" /> The [[cookbook]] has gone through many editions in its 100-year history. In 1955, a "De Luxe" edition was introduced, and had gone through 57 reprints by 2006.<ref>Edmonds Cookery Book, 2006</ref>
The book has been described as "as much a part of New Zealand kitchens as a stove and knife," and at one time it was "sent unsolicited to every newly engaged couple in New Zealand."<ref>Palenski, Ron: ''Kiwi Milestones : New Zealand's Population Through the Millions'' Hodder Moa Beckett, 2004 {{ISBN|978-1-86958-981-3}}</ref>
Edmonds recipe books have sold over 3,000,000 copies. It remains New Zealand's fastest selling book with over 200,000 copies sold in one year.
==Editions== The Edmonds Cookery Book has made several changes over its history to adapt to changing New Zealand tastes and new kitchen technology.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://edmondscooking.co.nz/cookery-books-history |title= Edmonds Cookery Book History |publisher= Edmonds |accessdate= 2 October 2016}}</ref>
