{{refimprove|date=June 2016}} {{Infobox Website | name = Lexipedia | url = http://www.lexipedia.com/ | commercial = | type = [[semantic network]] [[online dictionary]] [[online thesaurus]] | language = English, Dutch, French, German, Italian, Spanish | registration = | owner = [[Vantage Learning]] | launch date = June 2007 }} '''Lexipedia''' is an online visual [[semantic network]] with [[dictionary]] and [[thesaurus]] reference functionality built on [[Vantage Learning]]'s Multilingual ConceptNet.<ref>G. Adriaens. [https://web.archive.org/web/20070221083246/http://www.ccl.kuleuven.be/Courses/LEA/LEA-IR-Summ200203.pdf Language Engineering Applications: INFORMATION RETRIEVAL AND SUMMARIZATION]. ccl.kuleuven.be (2003-02-20)</ref> Lexipedia presents words with their semantic relationships displayed in an animated visual word web. Lexipedia contains an expanded version of the English [[Wordnet]] and supports six languages; English, Dutch, French, German, Italian, Spanish languages.
