{{about|the biological concept|the abstract category in linguistics|Morphome (linguistics)}}
{{no footnotes|date=February 2008}}
'''Morphome''' is one of the omes in [[biology]] to map and classify all the [[morphology (biology)|morphological]] features of [[species]]. Morphome is different from [[phenome]] in that it is the totality of morphological variants while phenome includes non-morphological variants.<ref>{{cite book|title=Characterization of the Drosophila segment determination morphome.|last1=Surkova |first1=S|last2=Kosman |first2=D|last3=Kozlov |first3=K|display-authors=etal|journal=Junior Developmental Biology|date=4 November 2007}}</ref>

